                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/7278: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-02-02T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 2, 1938—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>49. Your 79, January 31, 7 p.m. You may inform the Foreign Office that I shall
                    take an early opportunity to deplore on behalf of the American public recent
                    bombardments from the air of undefended and thickly populated cities.<note
                        n="15" xml:id="d104fn15">Similar instructions were sent to the Ambassador in
                        France in telegram No. 59, February 2, 6 p.m.</note> For your information, I
                    think it wiser to make such a statement complete in itself without relation to
                    expressions on the same subject by either the British or French Governments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
